Breeding adult.description: Lesser Yellowlegs have a smudgy neck and breast while nonbreeding and juvenile Wilson's Phalaropes have a white neck and breast. They also have longer legs and a thicker bill than Wilson's Phalaropes.

Nonbreeding adult.description: Lesser Yellowlegs have a smudgy neck and breast while nonbreeding and juvenile Wilson's Phalaropes have a white neck and breast. They also have longer legs and a thicker bill than Wilson's Phalaropes.

Juvenile.description: In flight, note the dark stripe down the tail and white stripes down the wings on Red Phalaropes but not on Wilson's Phalaropes, which have a white unstriped rump and plain grayish wings.

Nonbreeding.description: Nonbreeding Red-necked Phalaropes have a dark eye patch that Wilson's Phalaropes lack.
